Review: Finally — an Indian restaurant that delivers. This place is pure veg and served authentic dishes. The salty lassi, badam milk, malai kofta — everything was fresh and made from scratch. With tons of south Indian options too, it’s a clear cut favorite. Would definitely recommend.
Some of the best Thai food in the city. Cannot go wrong. Also great on doordash
All time Richmond classic. Red curry fried rice, veggie dumplings in panang sauce, spicy ramen. It is all excellent.
Great spot for corporate dinners. Excellent margs, nice unique menu (duck, octopus, umi, scallops). Lots of seafood options
Some of the best thin crust ever. Pesto sauce is incredible
Absolute banger slices. all the time.

Food was very average and resulted in instant diarrhea lmao — all the chaat’s tasted the same. Samosa was clearly frozen and defrosted. 

If you’re craving Indian food and don’t care about the taste of the physiological effect it will have on your body then this is the spot for you.

There was nothing special about the food — everything was a little too acidic. Hummus was average (much better places in the city). Lamb sausages were decent but dry. Falafel was pretty good. The grape leaves were probably best thing we had all night. 

Good to try once, not worth returning to.

Bottomless brunch and Gyros? Hard to resist. Awesome music in the restaurant, great decor, and incredibly good food, all for under $35/person. This is a must-eat at restaurant, and it’s conveniently located in East Village a short 5 minute walk from the 6 Train.
Unique New York twist on burgers
One of the best Italian spots in the city. Nothing on the menu is bad. I would sacrifice everything for Giano.
